@node requirements
@title "Requirements"

 This AmigaAMP skin requires AmigaAMP v2.0+ by Thomas Wenzel and  of  course  the
 Amiga 'Legacy' or 'Classic' edition.

 A graphic board is recommended, but not required, because of the relatively low
 colour depth (8 Bit) and the datatypes loading routine of AmigaAMP.

 Using it with recent PC versions of WinAMP is not  recommended  as  -  for  the
 moment  -  only those features were created that are supported by AmigaAMP v2.0
 so far.

@endnode

@node install
@title "How to install??"

 To install just grab the 'Legacy'  directory  and  drop  it  into  the  'Skins'
 sub-directory of AmigaAMP.

 It should not be that hard to install ...
 
@endnode

